{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-012__001__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-012", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 1, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·012.1", "chinese_text": "旄丘之葛兮，何誕之節兮，叔兮伯兮，何多日也。", "translation_ref": "旄丘.1", "translation_text": "The dolichos on that high and sloping mound; —\nHow wide apart are [now] its joints!\nO ye uncles,\nWhy have ye delayed these many days?"}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-012__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-012", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 2, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·012.2", "chinese_text": "何其處也，必有與也，何其久也，必有以也。", "translation_ref": "旄丘.2", "translation_text": "Why do they rest without stirring?\nIt must be they expect allies.\nWhy do they prolong the time?\nThere must be a reason for their conduct."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-012__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-012", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 3, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·012.3", "chinese_text": "狐裘蒙戎，匪車不東，叔兮伯兮，靡所與同。", "translation_ref": "旄丘.3", "translation_text": "Our fox-furs are frayed and worn.\nCame our carriages not eastwards?\nO ye uncles,\nYou do not sympathize with us."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-012__004__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-012", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 4, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·012.4", "chinese_text": "瑣兮尾兮，流離之子，叔兮伯兮，褎如充耳。", "translation_ref": "旄丘.4", "translation_text": "Fragments, and a remnant,\nChildren of dispersion [are we]!\nO ye uncles,\nNotwithstanding your full robes, your ears are stopped."}
